<p><img height="273" width="300" src="http://www.edenhrconsulting.com/images/stories/eden-stick-figures/eden-training.jpg" alt="eden-training" style="float: right;" />Sometimes referred to as Training Needs Analysis, is a really useful method of taking stock of the skills, talent and capabilities of the people within your Organisation. In short, it is a systematic approach of gathering data to establish the existing knowledge, skills and attitudes of employees, and identifies where there may be potential gaps in the skills knowledge within the Organisation.</p>
<p>A Training Needs Analysis exerciseÂ is usually undertaken to complement the business strategy, and its aim is the production of a development plan, which enables the Organisation to ensure there is sufficient capability to sustain business performance.</p>
<p>Eden can work with your business to identify skills gaps and future requirements within your business. This will involve looking at your strategy and the people within your business, and putting together a prioritisation of training against budgets. From here, we can identify the best solutions against financial outlay, maximising your return on investment.</p></td>
